OL,3,CResident doctors vote to continue
OL,4,Cstriking over next six months
OL,6,FThe re-ballot, which opened in early
OL,7,FDecember last year, asked doctors if
OL,8,Fthey are willing to act over a lack of
OL,9,Fjobs and pay erosion.
OL,11,FDr Jack Fletcher, chairman of the
OL,12,FBMA's resident doctors committee, said
OL,13,Fthis doesn't necessarily mean that
OL,14,Fthere will be more strikes.
OL,16,F"In recent weeks, the government has
OL,17,Fshown an improved approach in tone
OL,18,Fcompared with the name-calling we saw
OL,19,Flate last year.
